Grand Magi are elite arcane casters who maintain multiple elemental engagements simultaneously.
The title originates as a Solar Court civic honorific for arcanists sustaining parallel elemental forms.
The modern tradition revived during the Ash-and-Iron Decades, combining Sorcerer synthesis and Wizard formal methodology.
Core technique: layered elemental pressure where multiple elements reinforce each other for amplified effects.
Combat role is high-damage multi-element caster. Element combinations exceed individual elements in output.
The Convergence Codices from the Confluent Theorists provide the theoretical framework for multi-domain interaction.
Grand Magi synthesize the Chromatic Circle (Sorcerer) and Axiomatic Schools (Wizard) approaches.
This is a remort class requiring mastery of both Sorcerer and Wizard traditions.
Their methodology applies formal proof to multi-school interaction phenomena.
